body.description: Nature Made Super B Complex with Vitamin C and Folic Acid helps support the immune system and offers a combination of 8 essential B vitamins that support energy metabolism(1). Sourced from high-quality ingredients, these Nature Made Vitamin B complex tablets are a gluten free dietary supplement with no color added and no artificial flavors. This Nature Made Super B Complex provides all 8 essential B vitamins: thiamin (B1), riboflavin (B2), niacin (B3), pantothenic acid (B5), B6 (pyridoxine), biotin (B7), folic acid (B9), and B12 (cyanocobalamin). These Nature Made super B-complex with Vitamin C supplements also provide support for a healthy brain and nervous system. Adults take one of these Vitamin B complex supplements daily with water and a meal. Nature Made supplements are quality you can trust. USP has tested and verified ingredients, potency and manufacturing process. USP sets official standards for dietary supplements. Visit the USP verified website for more information. (1)Helps convert food into cellular energy. *Based on a survey of pharmacists who recommend branded vitamins and supplements.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: HELPS SUPPORT BRAIN CELL & NERVOUS SYSTEM FUNCTION PLUS VITAMIN C+ This B complex supplement supports brain cell and nervous system function and includes Vitamin C, an antioxidant that helps support the immune system.+ SUPPORTS ENERGY METABOLISM(1)+ Nature Made Super B-Complex contains a combination of all 8 essential B vitamins (thiamin, riboflavin, niacin, B6, folic acid, biotin, pantothenic acid and B12), which help brain and body cells produce the energy they need to function. Vitamin B6 supports the production of neurotransmitters needed for mood health.+ (1)Helps convert food into cellular energy.+ 1 DAILY TABLET FOR ADULTS Adults, take 1 tablet daily with water and a meal. HIGH QUALITY INGREDIENTS Meets our high-quality standards. Made from carefully selected ingredients under strict manufacturing processes. No color added, no artificial flavors, gluten free.

UNDERSTANDING VITAMIN B B vitamins help brain and body cells produce the energy they need to function. These essential nutrients are vital for converting food into cellular energy and support nervous system function. There are 8 B vitamins generally included in the B complex: Thiamin (B1), Riboflavin (B2), Niacin (B3), Pantothenic Acid (B5), B6 (Pyridoxine), Biotin (B7), Folic Acid (B9), and B12 (Cyanocobalamin). Vitamins B6, B9 (Folic Acid) and B12 are often linked with brain health. They work together to help brain and body cells produce SAM-e, which is important for mood health.+ Adequate intake of B vitamins is especially important for those who experience low energy, eat plant-based diets, and women of childbearing age or pregnant women.+ B vitamins are foundational to whole body health, but various factors can influence how much of these essential nutrients we need and consume daily. For example, Folic Acid (B9) is particularly important for pregnant women and women of childbearing age. Vitamin B12 is important for vegetarians and vegans who may not consume enough from their diet alone. Dietary supplements can help provide essential B vitamins that may be lacking in the diet.+

reviews.reviewText: The tablets are yellow, not too large, and relatively easy to swallow. The package arrived intact and not damaged. The expiration date was still 1.5+ years away. Be sure to drink plenty of water and stay hydrated or else your urine will be neon yellow

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Covers what I need
reviews.reviewText: As with all B vitamins it has the same “burp” taste, but covers all I need for vitamin B deficiency. Now taking daily pill instead of weekly/monthly shot.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Super B Complex
reviews.reviewText: I have been dealing with a genetic disorder and Chronic Fatigue Syndrome for years. I tend to have a lot of vitamin deficiencies which wreak havoc on my body. Anyway, this is a really great B Complex, plus a few other things like Vit C which can help further with absorption, which is good because I have issues with that as well. They do smell like vitamins, because they're vitamins. But when you really need them, that shouldn't stop you from taking them. They're easy to swallow, and they do seem to help with fatigue.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewText: very pleased with these B vitamins and especially happy with the low price

In spite of eating right, with advancing years, I have taken no chances on my system absorbing enough vitamins from food alone. Especially, since large scale farming, with simple fertilizers can deplete the soil, and thus the harvested produce, from multiple nutrients which we normally expect. Thus, along with other nutrients, I have taken this Nature Made multiple B vitamin suppliment every day for many years and trust in their quality.
